      "id": "f93ead111d9a5346249b099c9dc9250d7acd8765",
      "message": "Snowflake Dual JVM Work - Rationalise the JDBC_Connection (#14789)\n\n- Add Java RMI to enable Snowflake.\n- Merged the two `JDBC_Connection` log methods into one (now a private method).\n- Both environment variables will continue to work.\n- Privatised internal methods on `JDBC_Connection`.\n- Removed the use of `Connection.try_large_update` - simplifies the code and not an issue for less than 2BB rows changed.\n- Moved exception handling onto `JDBC_Connection.with_connection` so always handled (hence allowed me to remove `with_handled_connection`.\n- Remove `execute` on `JDBC_Connection` in favour of `Connection` handling it and using `with_prepared_statement`.\n- `SQLServer_Connection.execute` added to cope with anomaly in SQL Server JDBC support.\n- Removed workarounds for #7117 which has been fixed.\n- Adjusted `In_Transaction.ensure_in_transaction` so no returns an error rather than nesting level (reduce stack trace).",
      "timestamp": "2026-03-03T20:30:12Z",
      "author": {
        "name": "James Dunkerley"
      }
    }
  },
